    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-11-03T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-11-03T23:00:00-05:00" n="614"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d614">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.515/815: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-11-04T12:00:00+08:00"
                            >November 4, 1935—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received November 4—8
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Reference my strictly confidential November 2, 11 p.m., I am informed the British
                    authorities have issued an Order in Council advising British nationals to comply
                    with the decree of the Chinese Government regarding the nationalization of
                    silver.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
